I think a lot about the millennials who were the last generation able to create connections with artists without the pressure of having a critical eye.
We arrived during an age of gold for media, with a collective consciousness of pop culture that no longer exists.
We dove directly into things without worrying about the source, because it wasn't so easy to determine.
Without reason to question the pedestal on which we placed them, parasocial relationships had become foundations for our lives.
This is why we are so attached to nostalgia.
When The Office was still on, my friends and I would order pizzas and watch the show every Thursday.
This was nothing like what we have now with streaming, where 12 episodes are available all at once and everyone watches at their own pace, starting social media posts with "spoiler alert" or engaging in specific closed spaces.
Unconsciously, we longed to connect with the universal community that surrounded everything.
This is why so many of us watch shows like The Office or movies like The Devil Wears Prada with such obsession, filled with short references, just like memes.
We repeated these refs, knowing that most people were familiar with them.
now, even when something becomes completely viral, you can't know if everyone has seen it.
there are too many things to see and no way to rationalize it all... will we escape hyper-saturation?
we get caught up in cycles of discovering new media, only to realize that the artist is a predator or a fanatic.
we are forced to deal with a situation where we cling to nostalgia while acknowledging that the artists we connect with can be very imperfect.
we enter parasocial relationships with more awareness.
on comprend que c'est dur d'arriver à ces positions de richesse et de pouvoir sans écraser les autres en cours de route.
faute de conscience collective sur les médias, on a développé une conscience de classe qui nous aide à restez critiques.
certains d'entre nous continuent de placer des gens sur un piédestal, pour ensuite être choqués quand ils en tombent.
on est dans une période mouvementée et j'ai hâte de savoir où ça va nous mener.
